name: 1511 Concord Pkwy N, Concord, NC 28025, USA
directions: if you come in the front then just turn right and keep walking. if you come in a different way just walk to the far right end of the restaurant.
comment: it's fine to go to the bathroom and leave if you don't wanna buy anything, people do it all the time. they are gendered but are safe space. the men's only has one stall but it's handicap accessible.

name: McDonald's
directions: from the front entrance, turn right and just keep walking. from the other entrance, just walk to the far right end of the restaurant.
comment: you don't have to buy anything, plenty of people just go in to use the bathroom. they both have a handicap accessible stall and safe spaces in my opinion (as someone who works here)

name: Joann Fabrics

name: Relampago Coffee Lab
comment: Says you have to be a paying costumer but no one cares if you come in just to use the bathroom.

name: Westport High School
comment: These are almost always locked, or worse, rebranded as "adult only" bathrooms or just additional women's bathrooms. Hopefully the school unlocks these again in future years but I wouldn't hold my breath. Fuck this school, don't come here especially if you're trans

name: CVS
directions: Walking through the main doors, follow the center aisle all the way to the back wall. There will be red Rx pickup lockers. Turn right from standing directly in front of them. Slightly to the left, on the wall directly across from you, there are two single stall unisex restrooms.
comment: There was no toilet paper holder in the stall I used. The toilet paper was just sitting on the grab bar. The other stall had pee all over the toilet seat.

name: Birmingham Premiere LUX Cine GSX & Pizza Pub
directions: Behind ticketing counter. There are giant neon letters "M" and "W"
comment: You may need a movie ticket!

name: Sandia Resort & Casino
directions: From the main entrance, make an immediate right; family bathroom will be on the right hand side - sandwiched in between the Lightning Link Lounge and the P'a Shur Deli.

name: MOD coffeehouse
directions: To the left of the coffee bar
comment: Single room, turn lock indicates vacant/occupied

name: Walmart

name: Ginny's Teapot

comment: You need to get something from the café but it is a vegetarian and vegan place and you can just buy a drink.  It's a tight squeeze if 2 people are crossing on the stairs and there is nowhere to wait if someone is inside so you need to come back up again.

name: Bowman’s Beach

name: Mill Hollow & Bacon Woods

name: Toppers Pizza
comment: I don’t remember whether it was accessible or not for sure but I think it was. I do not remember whether there was a changing table or not. Very friendly staff.

name: Caswell’s Discount Warehouse

name: Coronado Center

name: 66 Returns

comment: The owner's will greet you, so say hi!

name: Forgotten Finds

name: Walmart

name: C. 50 115, B1900 La Plata, Provincia de Buenos Aires, Argentina
Green Door on 8th

name: Dalia's

name: Civic Media Center

The light is inside the bathroom.

Note: the bathrooms in the church hall across the street are gendered.

directions: Go in the front door and take an immediate right. Take another right and there are 2 bathrooms in that hallway.

name: Einstein Bros Bagels
directions: Near one of the entrances.

name: Mundelein Center for the Fine and Performing Arts
directions: Three entrances to this building. Enter and head toward the large theater doors (you will walk past a SINGLE freight elevator on your left; note that this is not the set of four elevators near the help desk). After passing the freight elevator, you will see a hallway on your left. Go down the hallway a few steps until you see the gender-neutral, single-occupancy door on your right (past the Womens restroom).
comment: Changing table. Paper towels (no loud hand dryers for those sensitive to loud sounds).

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: Enter store, turn left to walk toward dining area. Around the corner in a small hallway you will see two individual gender-neutral bathrooms (each bathroom has its own door with heavy bolt lock).
comment: No purchase necessary. Each bathroom also has an electrical outlet and a needle disposal box on the wall. Usually very clean.

name: Maine Film Center

comment: This is not obvious; you really need to know where you’re going. It is also possible to get there by using stairs from the lobby, but I don’t think one can do that without a ticket.

name: Carmel Clay Public Library
